    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "A *potion of annulment* magically breaks a supernatural deal you have made, such as an infernal contract (Bestiary 90), a sea hag's bargain, or the *geas* ritual.  \n  \n Upon drinking the potion, attempt a counteract check against the highest-level such effect, with a counteract modifier determined by the potion's type. If the check is successful, the deal ends for all parties. You're not penalized for breaking the contract, but you also enjoy none of its benefits or rewards. Individuals with whom you shared the contract are aware it has been annulled and may seek vengeance. This potion can't rewind time or negate effects that have already occurred; for example, if you have killed someone to fulfill an infernal contract, drinking this potion and canceling the contract doesn't bring the dead individual back to life.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 137,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "rare"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Rare",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "legacy",
        "game-id": "fd5735184d8cc7e06debda7ae557fa0d",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Abjuration",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "4.0",
              "aonid": 1,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "4.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Core Rulebook pg. 628",
              "aonid": 1,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Core Rulebook pg. 628",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Core Rulebook",
            "page": 628,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Effects and magic items with this trait are associated with the abjuration school of magic, typically involving protection or wards.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 36,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "07336d377bbfcf8d760f34f32f513526",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Consumable",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 454",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 454",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 454,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "An item with this trait can be used only once. Unless stated otherwise, it\u2019s destroyed after activation. Consumable items include alchemical items and magical consumables such as scrolls and talismans. A character can Craft consumable items in batches of four.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 130,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "6046ffa09feee37a486ec66f5e30d7a7",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Potion",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 459",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 459",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 459,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A potion is a consumable magical liquid activated when you drink it.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
